comment: Caldwell-Pope (DET) tips the ball into the backcourt and the ball is loose when Paul (LAC) recovers it.
Jackson (DET) slips the contact and makes incidental contact with Griffin (LAC), who maintains a legal guarding position outside the RA under the rim.
Jordan (LAC) sets the screen on Jackson (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact. Jackson slips and falls, but not as a result of any contact.
Tolliver (DET) makes contact with Jordan's (LAC) head on his made dunk attempt.
Paul (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Jackson's (DET) drive.
Jackson (DET) gathers the ball and then jumps from his right foot, landing on both feet. He then legally jumps again, releasing the ball before he returns to the floor.
Paul (LAC) maintains legal guarding position on the play to the basket by Jackson (DET).
Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes incidental contact with Redick (LAC) that does not affect his FOM.
[Observable in enhanced video] Paul (LAC) splits his feet on the perimeter.
Johnson (LAC) applies a forearm/hand to the front of Jackson (DET) above the free-throw line extended. This is an automatic foul. Contact also affects RSBQ.
Jordan (LAC) sets the screen on Morris (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Redick (LAC) grabs Drummond (DET) on the made FTA.
Morris (DET) makes contact with Crawford's (LAC) body that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
The contact from Drummond (DET) is incidental and does not affect Griffin's (LAC) ability to make the pass.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes contact with Johnson's (LAC) arm and affects his ability to maintain possession of the ball.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes incidental contact with Redick (LAC) on the perimeter.
Griffin (LAC) makes incidental foot to foot contact with Drummond (DET) on the rebound attempt.
[Incidental or immaterial] Jackson (DET) and Jordan (LAC) engage briefly in transition.

Since play originates inside the lower defensive box, Drummond (DET) may be in the restricted area to defend Griffin's (LAC) shot. However, RHH shows that he makes contact with Griffin's shooting arm, preventing his follow through.
Drummond (DET) never fully clears the paint and is in without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Jordan (LAC) makes contact with Drummond's (DET) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Griffin (LAC) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Drummond (DET) sets the screen on Paul (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Drummond (DET) makes contact with Griffin's (LAC) body that affects his shot attempt.
Rivers (LAC) makes contact with Jackson's (DET) arm as he starts his upward shooting motion.
Baynes (DET) sets the screen on Rivers (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Rivers (LAC) maintains legal guarding position on the play to the basket by Jackson (DET).
Griffin (LAC) and Caldwell-Pope (DET) briefly engage and separate off the ball.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) trips Griffin (LAC) on his drive to the basket.
Jordan (LAC) makes contact with Caldwell-Pope's (DET) body that affects his shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Drummond (DET) makes incidental contact with Griffin (LAC) that does not affect his ability to make the pass.
Baynes (DET) sets the screen on Redick (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Rivers (LAC) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
Griffin (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Drummond's (DET) shot attempt.
Johnson (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Jackson's (DET) shot attempt.
